options.systemMessage:
=Please analyze the following job description in the user message against the candidate.

Additional JOB DATA:
- Title: {{ $('Filter').item.json.title }}
- Company: {{ $('Filter').item.json.companyName }}
- applyUrl: {{ $('Filter').item.json.applyUrl }}
- jobUrl: {{ $('Filter').item.json.jobUrl }}
- postedTime: {{ $('Filter').item.json.postedTime }}

CANDIDATE PROFILE:
- Skills: Python, SQL, Risk, Underwriting, AML, Machine Learning, Data Visualization, n8n, Ai Agents, Prompt Engineering
- Experience: 5 years

---
Output the JSON with missing_skills, fit_summary, and cover_letter_draft.

missing_skills -> Anything in the job description not in the candidate skills section

fit_summary -> 1 sentance describing the fit based on the profile

cover_letter_draft -> short paragraph used for an application. What a canidate uses to apply with.

parameters.jsonSchemaExample:
{
  "job_analysis": {
    "job_title": "Senior DevOps Engineer",
    "fit_summary": "Candidate has 6 years of experience with Kubernetes and AWS which aligns with the core requirements.",
    "missing_skills": [
      "Azure DevOps",
      "Istio"
    ],
    "application_materials": {
      "tailored_cover_letter": "...",
      "linkedin_dm": "..."
    },
    "metadata": {
      "apply_url": "https://linkedin.com/apply/...",
      "job_url": "https://linkedin.com/jobs/view/...",
      "posted_time": "2 hours ago"
    }
  }
}

parameters.text:
=🎯 *New High-Match Job Found!*
*Role:* {{ $json.output.job_analysis.job_title }}

*Experience Level:* {{ $('Filter').item.json.experienceLevel }}

🔥 *Missing Skills:* {{ $json.output.job_analysis.missing_skills }}

Apply link: {{ $json.output.job_analysis.metadata.apply_url }}

Job link: {{ $json.output.job_analysis.metadata.job_url }}
